steg_functions - contains all the functions/library dependencies necessary to run the other steg scripts. Please edit the other steg scripts to have the correct path to this file on your system

lemonjuice - encode two/three ascii messages in a library of double stranded DNA duplexes

baking_soda - encode three binary image files in a library of double stranded DNA duplexes

ShortRefGlobalAligner - A short reference global aligner written by Dario Beraldi (https://github.com/dariober/bioinformatics-cafe/tree/master/eclipse/ShortRefGlobalAligner)

raw2srga - trim raw fastq file and align with SRGA

raw2srga_split - same as raw2srga but splits the raw fastq file by inline barcodes

steg_draft - create a draft reference sequence from the output of SRGA

steg_decode_text - Decode to TEXT. Command line program, controlled with argument flags. Runs in different modes depending on if input data is from sequencing, BS-sequencing or oxBS-sequencing. In BS mode can have 5mC position list supplied for application of a switching cipher

steg_decode_images - Decode to IMAGE. Command line run program, controlled with argument flags. Runs in different modes depending on if input data is from sequencing, BS-sequencing or oxBS-sequencing. In BS mode can have 5mC position list supplied for application of a switching cipher


R version 3.1.1 (2014-07-10) was used throughout [R Core Team (2014). R: A language and environment for statistical computing. R Foundation for Statistical Computing, Vienna, Austria. URL http://www.R-project.org/].

Please contact grm32(at)cam.ac.uk, cm771(at)cam.ac.uk or pm473(at)cam.ac.uk for support.

